-- Datang Power shares surge after deal to restructure coal chemical business 
-- By Grace Li
-- Mon Jul 07, 2014 09:53PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, July 8 (Reuters) - H-Shares of Datang International Power Generation <0991.HK> <601991.SS> surged as much as 21.5 percent in resumed trade on Tuesday, after the company announced a deal to restructure its coal chemical business.

The power producer said late on Monday that it had signed a framework agreement with China Reform Holdings Corporation Ltd to sell its coal-chemical and related assets. [ID:L4N0PI39W]